  "decision_conditions": [
    "REASON:  The design, appearance, materials and method of illumination of the proposed fascia sign and proposed projecting sign would be harmful to the character and appearance of the host building, the amenity of the streetscene and the character and appearance of the surrounding conservation areas. The proposed signage is contrary to paragraph 67 of the National Planning Policy Framework 2012, policies 7.4 (Local Character), 7.5 (Public Realm) and 7.6 (Architecture) of the London Plan 2011, CS8 (Enhancing Islington's Character) and CS9 of the Islington Core Strategy 2011, policies Env11 (Advertisements and Signs), D13 (shopfronts) and D34 (Advertisements) of the Islington Unitary Development Plan 2002, section 2.6.2 (Advertising and Signs) of the Islington Urban Design Guide 2006, guidance contained within the Conservation Area Design Guidelines 2002 and Islington's Shopfront Design Guide 2003, and emerging policies DM1 (Design), DM3 (Heritage), and DM6 (Advertisements) of Islington's Development Management Policies Document Submission Version 2012."
